                            <comment id="13068602" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2011 21:15:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;adds appends and has append return a DataByteArray.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13122248" author="alangates" created="Thu, 6 Oct 2011 21:23:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Reviewing this patch, seriously belatedly. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130772" author="alangates" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 18:07:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Reviewing this patch it looks fine.  But every time I run the tests on it I see quite a few test failures.  The failures are not repeatable, nor is it the same tests failing.  But it&apos;s frequent enough that I&apos;m convinced something here is causing an issue.  I&apos;ll keep looking into it, but at this point I want to hold off committing this patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130806" author="thejas" created="Wed, 19 Oct 2011 18:38:47 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I also verified that adding new functions to an existing class is a binary compatible change - &lt;a href=&quot;http://java.sun.com/docs/books/jls/second_edition/html/binaryComp.doc.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://java.sun.com/docs/books/jls/second_edition/html/binaryComp.doc.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13229752" author="daijy" created="Wed, 14 Mar 2012 23:27:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I run through the tests. I checked the patch seems nothing will break existing code. I plan to commit the patch, objection?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13229756" author="alangates" created="Wed, 14 Mar 2012 23:29:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As long as the tests pass consistently, no objections.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
